# harness/intake.config — config-driven intake.
#
# Deployed enforcement-protected file: agent edits are floor-denied; changes are authored as sandbox/ candidates and human-spliced under FORGE_ALLOW_HOOK_EDIT=1 (audit-logged).
#
# Mirrors the targets.config / beads.config idiom: intake.sh hardcodes NO paths or defaults — it reads
# them here. Pointing intake at a different template or specs dir is a config edit, not a code edit.
# KEY=VALUE; sourced by harness/intake.sh. Env overrides win (tests point INTAKE_SPECS_DIR at a tmp dir).
#
# SINGLE-WRITER: intake is a human-front-door lifecycle — run ONE `intake.sh start` at a time. The next
# NNN scan and the same-slug clobber check are read-then-act, so concurrent starts are NOT supported; a
# same-NNN race fails closed on the atomic leaf `mkdir` rather than silently overwriting. No lock, no queue.
# `start` now also refuses while an intake sentinel is already active (finish via ratify/convert, or abort).

# --- template + output layout ----------------------------------------------
# Paths resolve against the repo ROOT unless already absolute.
INTAKE_TEMPLATE="${INTAKE_TEMPLATE:-templates/spec-template.md}"   # the live spec template
INTAKE_SPECS_DIR="${INTAKE_SPECS_DIR:-specs}"                      # scaffolds specs/NNN-<slug>/spec.md

# --- intake defaults --------------------------------------------------------
INTAKE_MODE_DEFAULT="${INTAKE_MODE_DEFAULT:-interactive}"          # --mode default: interactive (human in the loop)

# --- clarify loop ------------------------------------------------------------
# The clarify ROUND budget bounds agent-initiated QUESTIONS, never spec COVERAGE (F1: route, never drop):
# every eligible ambiguity past the budget becomes a flagged [ASSUMED ...] in ## Assumptions, with NO cap.
# Tunable, not a baked magic number. A human may always grant another round (`intake.sh clarify`), even at
# zero remaining — intent-clarity outranks the quota. The budget is snapshotted into the intake sentinel at
# `start`, so the Stop gate and the (canary-gated) clarify-gate read one source of truth.
INTAKE_CLARIFY_ROUNDS="${INTAKE_CLARIFY_ROUNDS:-5}"   # max agent-initiated clarify rounds (= AskUserQuestion calls)
INTAKE_RESTATE_ROUNDS="${INTAKE_RESTATE_ROUNDS:-3}"   # max Gate-A restatement rounds before a forced ## UNRECONCILED
INTAKE_CLARIFY_MAX_Q="${INTAKE_CLARIFY_MAX_Q:-4}"     # defensive per-call question cap (the AskUserQuestion tool itself caps at 4)

# Runaway backstop for the intake Stop gate (mirrors FORGE_STOP_BLOCK_CAP): FORGE_INTAKE_BLOCK_CAP (default 8),
# read from the environment by .claude/hooks/stop-gate-intake.sh — not sourced here.

# --- intake profiles (P6b) ---------------------------------------------------
# `intake.sh start --profile <name>` selects a preset that shapes intake ERGONOMICS only. The profile is
# ADVISORY (recorded in the spec Header + the intake sentinel) and the acceptance gate is PROFILE-BLIND.
# Presets live in a separate config (mirrors the targets.config idiom); resolve it against ROOT.
INTAKE_PROFILES="${INTAKE_PROFILES:-harness/intake-profiles.config}"   # the profile presets file
INTAKE_PROFILE_DEFAULT="${INTAKE_PROFILE_DEFAULT:-code}"               # --profile default
